  "prompt": "If I leave Aloe Vera gel on my face overnight and wash it in the morning, do I wash it with soap or just water? And can I put moisturizer after?",
  "response": "When using Aloe Vera gel on your face overnight, here\u2019s how to care for your skin in the morning:\n\n1. **Washing**:  \n   - It\u2019s best to wash your face with just **water** in the morning. Aloe Vera gel is light and typically doesn\u2019t leave a heavy residue, so a gentle rinse with lukewarm water is usually enough to remove it.  \n   - If your skin feels sticky or you prefer a deeper cleanse, you can use a **gentle, non-drying cleanser** or soap. Avoid harsh soaps that might strip your skin\u2019s natural oils.\n\n2. **Moisturizer**:  \n   - After washing, it\u2019s a good idea to apply a **moisturizer**. While Aloe Vera is hydrating, it\u2019s not a substitute for a moisturizer, especially if you have dry skin.  \n   - Choose a lightweight, non-comedogenic moisturizer to lock in hydration without clogging your pores.\n\nConsistency is key! This routine can help soothe, hydrate, and nourish your skin over time.",
